  <walkingDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Other popular walks</strong> <strong>include:</strong> Loen is one of the best of our Norway resorts for walking opportunities with options for all levels, and many starting from the village centre. Many are signposted but we recommend you also purchase a more detailed map locally (approx. NOK80).</p>
<p><strong>Easy: </strong>Stroll along both sides of Lake Loen towards Olden for lovely scenery with the serene lake below and mountains above.</p>
<p><strong>Moderate:</strong>  Head to the Lodalen valley road through the Saeten pastures to Vassenden where the lake meets the river Olden You can also explore this area on one of our Wanderwalks. Nearby Stryn and Hornindal also offer further marked walking trails.</p>
<p><strong>Slightly Challenging:</strong> There are hiking routes near the Briksdal glacier, and you can get a guide for glacier guide on one of the nearby glacial arms. Or take the Fjord Trail from Tjugen towards Mount Skåla at 1,848m for fantastic views even if you don’t want to go all the way to the top.</p>]]></walkingDescription>
